HEADWORD: Lithia
<hw>Lith"i*a</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧th"⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>li`qos</grk> stone.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The oxide of lithium; a strong alkaline caustic similar to potash
and soda, but weaker. See <er>Lithium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lithia emerald</b></col>. <cd>See
<er>Hiddenite</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithiasis</ent>⟦br⟧
